    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-07T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-07T11:40:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1180.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-07T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1914, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Government in good faith after much trouble has assembled Congress to hear
                    protests as promised and for serious financial legislation. Members threaten to
                    cause chaos unless December salaries are paid them. Situation menacing
                    governmental order and I urge at request of Dominican Government that within the
                    day Department orders Receivership to advance $20,000 of Dominican Government
                    money to Minister of Finance. I deem this action imperative as Government has
                    reached end of resources and this action in my opinion will continue the orderly
                    condition which obtains here until permanent relief is devised. Delegates and I
                    insisted upon calling this Congress and the Government yielded notwithstanding
                    hostile majority. This advance would be used to pay senators, deputies and
                    important civil employees under the budget. Situation depending upon speedy
                    action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
